You can change the text flow direction by using the CSS property `direction: rtl` (cf. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/direction), like this:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    div {
      direction: rtl;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;section id=&quot;func1&quot;&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;function&quot;&gt; :ÿØÿ≥ÿ™Ÿàÿ± ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input id=&quot;function&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; value=&quot;x*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;derivative&quot;&gt; :ŸÖÿ¥ÿ™ŸÇ ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input type=text id=&quot;der&quot; value=&quot;2*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;color&quot;&gt;:ŸÑŸàŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÜÿ≠ŸÜŸâ &lt;/label&gt; &lt;input type=color id=&quot;color&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/section&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Simply put a `dir` attribute with the value of `rtl`, like this:  `dir=&quot;rtl&quot;` 

Check the snippet:


&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: null --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div dir=&quot;rtl&quot;&gt;
        &lt;section id=&quot;func1&quot;&gt;
          &lt;label for=&quot;function&quot;&gt; :ÿØÿ≥ÿ™Ÿàÿ± ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
          &lt;input id=&quot;function&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; value=&quot;x*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;label for=&quot;derivative&quot;&gt; :ŸÖÿ¥ÿ™ŸÇ ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
          &lt;input type=text id=&quot;der&quot; value=&quot;2*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          &lt;label for=&quot;color&quot;&gt;:ŸÑŸàŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÜÿ≠ŸÜŸâ &lt;/label&gt;  &lt;input type=color id=&quot;color&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/section&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

You Can use Direction in a three ways i.e `ltr` , `rtl` and `auto` 

**Syntax**

    &lt;element dir=&quot;ltr|rtl|auto&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .direction{
      direction: rtl;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;direction&quot;&gt;
      &lt;section id=&quot;func1&quot;&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;function&quot;&gt; :ÿØÿ≥ÿ™Ÿàÿ± ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input id=&quot;function&quot; type=&quot;text&quot; value=&quot;x*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;derivative&quot;&gt; :ŸÖÿ¥ÿ™ŸÇ ÿßŸÑÿØÿßŸÑÿ© 1 &lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input type=text id=&quot;der&quot; value=&quot;2*x&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;label for=&quot;color&quot;&gt;:ŸÑŸàŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÜÿ≠ŸÜŸâ &lt;/label&gt; &lt;input type=color id=&quot;color&quot; onchange=&quot;plot();&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/section&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


 1. ltr - Default. Left-to-right text direction
 2. rtl - Right-to-left text direction
 3. auto - Let the browser figure out the text direction, based on the content (only recommended if the text direction is unknown)

checkout more documentation about Direction [Here][1]


  [1]: https://www.w3schools.com/tags/att_global_dir.asp

